  'menu.section.browse_global': 'Browse DSpace',
  'register-page.registration.info': 'Register an account to subscribe to collections for email updates, and submit new items to Bhasha Sanchika.',
  'repository.title.prefix': '',
  'info.help.title': 'Help',
  'info.about.title': 'About',
  'coar-notify-support.ldn-inbox.content': 'For your convenience, our LDN (Linked Data Notifications) InBox is easily accessible at https://sanchika.ciil.org/server/ldn/inbox. The LDN InBox enables seamless communication and data exchange, ensuring efficient and effective collaboration.',
  'about.badge': 'About',
  'about.title.html': 'About <span>Us</span>',
  'about.section.introduction': 'Introduction',
  'about.intro.text': 'Welcome to <strong>Bhasha Sanchika</strong>, the digital language repository of the Central Institute of Indian Languages (CIIL), where language preservation, dissemination, and technological advancement converge in a pioneering initiative. Established in 1969, CIIL plays a pivotal role in the multifaceted landscape of language development and research in India. One of its primary functions is to advise and assist both the Central and State Governments on language-related matters, fostering linguistic harmony and promoting the learning of <strong>20 Indian languages</strong> by non-native speakers.',
  'about.section.commitment': 'CIIL\'s Commitment',
  'about.commitment.text': 'CIIL\'s commitment extends to the development of all Indian languages, exemplified through the creation of content and corpora. The institute is dedicated to protecting and documenting minor, minority, and tribal languages, recognizing their cultural significance. The institute\'s responsibilities encompass language analysis, pedagogy, technology, and use, addressing challenges in education, literacy, mass media, governance, and emotional integration. Moreover, CIIL functions as a catalyst for convergence of diverse disciplines and institutions, fostering collaboration and idea exchange.',
  'about.feature.title': 'Introducing<br>Bhasha Sanchika',
  'about.feature.desc': 'A dedicated step launched as a dynamic digital archive contributing to the bonds of unity among different Indian languages.',
  'about.feature.powered-by': 'Powered By:',
  'about.feature.dspace': 'D-Space Platform',
  'about.feature.opensource': 'Open Source',
  'about.section.journey': 'Our Journey',
  'about.timeline.2024.year': '2024',
  'about.timeline.2024.title': 'Foundation',
  'about.timeline.2024.desc': 'Foundation Stone for Starting Bhasha Sanchika',
  'about.timeline.2025.year': '2025',
  'about.timeline.2025.title': 'Bhasha Sanchika Launch',
  'about.timeline.2025.desc': 'Transitioning into a world-class digital repository for the modern era.',
  'about.timeline.2026.year': '2026',
  'about.timeline.2026.title': 'Bhasha Sanchika Ver.2',
  'about.timeline.2026.desc': 'Launch of Bhasha Sanchika Version 2.0 with enhanced features and improved user experience.',
  'about.section.objectives': 'Core Objectives',
  'about.obj.preservation.title': 'Preservation',
  'about.obj.preservation.desc': 'Ensuring the enduring storage of linguistic and cultural data.',
  'about.obj.digital.title': 'Digital Presence',
  'about.obj.digital.desc': 'Enhancing Indian languages and mother tongues across the web.',
  'about.obj.formats.title': 'Diverse Formats',
  'about.obj.formats.desc': 'Resources available in text, image, audio, and video formats.',
  'about.obj.langtech.title': 'Language Tech',
  'about.obj.langtech.desc': 'Creating technology resources and pedagogy materials for all.',
  'about.heritage.title': 'Explore India\'s Rich Linguistic Heritage',
  'about.heritage.text': 'In essence, <strong>Bhasha Sanchika</strong> emerges as a comprehensive digital repository aligning with national initiatives such as <strong>NEP-2020, Ek Bharat Shreshtha Bharat, Digital India, and Atmanirbhar Bharat</strong>. Beyond preserving linguistic diversity, it serves as a catalyst for research, education, and the promotion of Indian languages in the digital age.',
  'about.heritage.tag.nep': 'NEP-2020',
  'about.heritage.tag.digital': 'Digital India',
  'about.heritage.tag.atmanirbhar': 'Atmanirbhar Bharat',
  'about.heritage.tag.ekbharat': 'Ek Bharat Shreshtha Bharat',
  'about.section.specialised': 'Specialised Sections',
  'about.tab.sppel': 'SPPEL',
  'about.tab.bhasha': 'Bhasha Mandakini',
  'about.tab.bharat': 'Bharatavani',
  'about.tab.ciil': 'CIIL Publications',
  'about.sppel.title': 'SPPEL',
  'about.sppel.text': 'The dedicated Scheme for Protection and Preservation of Endangered Languages (SPPEL) focuses on endangered mother tongues and languages. This section encompasses raw audio files, transcriptions, translations, photographs, and videos to document languages at risk.',
  'about.bhasha.title': 'Bhasha Mandakini',
  'about.bhasha.text': 'This section features video documentaries covering various aspects of Bangla, Marathi, Kannada, and Tamil language and literature. These visual resources contribute to a deeper understanding of cultural nuances and literary history.',
  'about.bharat.title': 'Bharatavani',
  'about.bharat.text': 'Providing brief details of content in 121 languages, Bharatavani provides a portal for reading and downloading books collected from various sources across India. It acts as a single point of reference for knowledge in and about Indian languages.',
  'about.ciil.title': 'CIIL Publications',
  'about.ciil.text': 'An overview of all CIIL publications, potentially including scanned copies of rare academic books, linguistic research papers, and pedagogical materials available on the Bharatavani portal for public access.',
  'about.section.leadership': 'Our Leadership',
  'about.leader1.name': 'Prof. Shailendra Mohan',
