  'contrib.badge': 'Credits',
  'contrib.title.html': 'Contributors <span>Page</span>',
  'contrib.section.initiative': 'About the Initiative',
  'contrib.intro.p1': 'The <strong>Bhasha Sanchika</strong>, a digital language repository by the Central Institute of Indian Languages (CIIL), stands as a testament to the collective efforts dedicated to preserving Indian languages. Established over 56 years ago, CIIL actively engages diverse stakeholders in its mission. Collaboration is the linchpin, weaving together government initiatives, educational institutions, technological innovations, and grassroots community involvement.',
  'contrib.intro.p2': 'This collaborative approach is crucial in navigating the intricate landscape of linguistic diversity in India, ensuring that the repository becomes a shared resource for language preservation, dissemination, and technological advancement. We take this opportunity to acknowledge all the contributions that made Bhasha Sanchika a reality',
